  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always rented an apartment or found some kind of abode where we could stay because we never knew how long they would let us stay, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The presence of foreigners was immediately obvious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I still managed in Cahors-- this is one of the places that I mentioned-- to, to, to go to school because I had missed quite a lot of school time, until the day that the gendarmes came and arrested my father and sent him to a concentration camp in the South of France.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the day after, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] maybe it was even on the same afternoon-- that I'm not sure anymore, but definitely within a very short time, either the same day or the day after-- they came and arrested me, my mother, and my brother, and brought us also to that camp in France in, in the South of France.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That camp was called Agde, A-G-D-E, right on the Mediterranean.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What has always amazed me-- and still does-- is the zeal, I might also say the viciousness, with which the French police and authorities collaborated with the Germans in the apprehension of Jews.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] To give you an example, when we were arrested in Cahors, they thought nothing of delegating two gendarmes to escort us by train-- us meaning my mother, my little brother, and me, barely a teenager at the time-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to escort us all the way, under guard, from Cahors to the camp.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they didn't relax their vigilance until they handed us over to the guards in the camp, which is quite a-- quite a-- quite a trip.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Two guards for three people-- a mother and two-- and two children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
